      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start for the report. I've noticed some people online saying that these kinds of density laws actually end up hurting regular people, like making rent way too high or pushing older neighborhoods out. Do you think those concerns are valid or are they just misunderstanding how it works?",
